AGI - Three armed men broke into Nor Nork's police station in the Armenian capital, Yerevan. According to the first information, a grenade was exploded near the building and two of the commando were injured. The third, holding a hand bomb, appeared on the door and said he had asked for the resignation of Prime Minister Nikol Pashinyan.&nbsp; Armenian police chief Aram Hovhannisyan, arrived on the spot, tried to deal with the assailant for almost two hours to convince him to surrender. Meanwhile, other policemen, ambulances and emergency services arrived at the police station. The area has been transennata. The man, then, was arrested by the special forces, who had entered the police station building passing through the back entrance. To confirm the arrest was the spokesman of the Armenian Interior Ministry, Narek Sarkisyan. The two wounded were taken to the hospital: have lesions to moderate gravity legs. &nbsp;
